subSubSection.paragraph:
Female.
Antenna relatively shorter (
Fig. 12
), about 0.7X length of body. Spermathecal cornu (
Fig. 14
) slender, dorsally flattened; middle part long, apically and strongly curved, slightly widened near cornu; nodulus spherical, large; proximal spermathecal duct long, widest near nodulus, tightly coiled. Dorsal part of bursa-sclerites (
Fig. 15
) with teeth at apex, extending into middle of dorsal surface, basally widened; ventral part (
Fig. 13
) slender, with one row of teeth along inner margin.
